Brute Force Flow

For each node:

Take its value = x
Compute required value = k - x
Search the BST for k - x
If found and it's not the same node → return true
O(NLOGN) OR O(N2)

Optimal Approach (Striver's Iterator Method)
Think of BST as a sorted array:

2 3 4 5 6 7
Use:
one iterator from smallest (left)
one iterator from largest (right)

Just like Two Sum on a sorted array.
i = 2
j = 7

2+7 = 9
Found.


